## Data Pipeline

```text
Raw Energy Data
        ↓
Python Data Cleaning
        ↓
Feature Engineering
        ↓
KPI Construction
        ↓
CSV Export
        ↓
Power BI Data Model
        ↓
Interactive Dashboards
```

---

## Feature Engineering

Several analytical indicators were engineered using Python:

### Renewable Share

```text
Renewable Share =
Renewable Consumption /
Primary Energy Consumption
```

Measures the level of renewable energy penetration.

---

### Fossil Dependency

```text
Fossil Dependency =
Fossil Fuel Consumption /
Primary Energy Consumption
```

Measures dependency on fossil fuels.

---

### Energy Intensity Proxy

```text
Energy Intensity =
Primary Energy Consumption /
Electricity Generation
```

Used as a proxy for structural energy efficiency.

---

### Consumption Growth

```text
YoY Change =
(Current Consumption - Previous Consumption)
/
Previous Consumption
```

Measures annual changes in energy demand.

---

### Transition Gap

```text
Transition Gap =
Fossil Dependency - Renewable Share
```

A custom metric developed to quantify energy transition risk.

---

## Power BI Data Model

The dashboard follows a star schema architecture:

```text
                dim_country
                     |
                     |
dim_date ---- fact_energy
```

### Fact Table
- fact_energy

### Dimension Tables
- dim_country
- dim_date

---

# Dashboard Structure

## Page 1 — European Energy Market Overview

Provides a macro-level view of European energy markets:

- Total energy consumption
- Renewable energy share
- Fossil fuel dependency
- Historical consumption trends
- Country-level comparisons

---

## Page 2 — Energy Transition Analysis

Focuses on the transition towards cleaner energy systems:

- Renewable energy ranking
- Fossil dependency ranking
- Transition gap analysis
- Energy transition positioning scatter plot

---

## Page 3 — Energy Efficiency & Risk Analysis

Analyzes structural energy risks and efficiency:

- Energy intensity benchmarking
- Consumption volatility analysis
- Energy risk segmentation
- Transition risk ranking

---

## Key Insights

The analysis reveals substantial differences among European countries regarding:

- Renewable energy adoption
- Fossil fuel dependency
- Structural energy efficiency
- Transition risk exposure

Countries with high renewable penetration and low fossil dependency demonstrate lower transition risk and greater resilience.

